headline: 3 Reasons to Buy Target Stock Like There's No Tomorrow
summary: Target (NYSE: TGT) missed the mark for shareholders with a disappointing third-quarter earnings report.  Comparable sales from the retail giant grew just 0.3% year over year for the period ended Nov. 2, while adjusted earnings per share (EPS) of $1.85 fell well below the company's guidance range of $2.10 to $2.40.  The headline numbers may not inspire much confidence, but a deeper look highlights plenty of positives for investors to consider.
